The paper discusses the design and optimization of network topologies for communication patterns, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper specifically mentions demand-aware datacenter interconnects (cs.DC) and demand-aware overlay networks (cs.SI) as examples of the types of topologies they are interested in. The paper also discusses the entropy of communication matrices, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes a novel family of network topologies that are designed to optimize communication patterns, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or optimization (cs.OC).
